27/03/2006
TETOVO, Macedonia -- Police have uncovered an illegal arms depot in the Tetovo region, between the villages of Brodec and Vesala, the interior ministry announced on Sunday (26 March).
According to the statement, the cache of arms and ammunition was discovered after a tip.
Police say the depot most likely dates back to the 2001 interethnic conflict.
(Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 26/03/06)
